The KwaZulu-Natal Department of Transport will be opening some of its licence testing centres on weekends during the month of June. Residents of Pietermaritzburg and the Midlands will be able to go to the Mkondeni centre on June 5 and 6, June 12 and 13, June 19 and 20 and June 26 and 27 between 7 am and 1 pm to get assistance with the following: • Drivers and PRDP licence renewals; • Collection of driver's licences; • Booking of learner's and driver's licences; and • Learner's licence tests. Members of the public must also bring an eye certificate from an optometrist that is not older than three months. These services will also be offered at the Rossburgh testing centre in Durban between 7.30 am and 1.30 pm on all Saturdays and Sundays in June, while the Empangeni and Pinetown centres will operate between 7 am and 1 pm on weekends. Several municipal testing centres will also be open on Saturdays in June. In Verulam and KwaDakuza (Stanger) residents can get help from 7 am to 2 pm; while at Winklespruit the operating hours are from 7 am to 2pm. The Ray Nkonyeni (Port Shepstone) centre will be open from 8 am to 12 noon. Please note that, due to the Covid-19 pandemic, testing centres will be limiting the number of customers to comply with government regulations. For more detailed information regarding learner's licences and driver's licences, including renewals and PrDPs, go to http://www.kzntransport.gov.za